CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 20, 1960, pg. B10 reads: "Chi Delta Mu Fraternity Entertains Lavishly - Dr. Oliver King, far right, with Mrs. King at his side, and guests." Portion of accompanying article published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 20, 1960, pg. A7 by Toki Schalk Johnson reads:"Wednesday brought forth the annual dinner dance given by the Chi Delta Mu Fraternity in beautifully decorated New Arena."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of four men, including Dr. Oliver King, right, and five women, including Mrs. Oliver King, second from right, seated at rectangular banquet table for Chi Delta Mu dinner dance in New Arena Supper Club
